    "description": "Join us for a day that’s about more than just golf — it’s about making a real difference.\n\nThe Swing for Independence Charity Golf Day is raising funds to support Kerry Walsh, a South African SMA warrior, motivational speaker, author of Finding My Feet, and disability advocate. This event supports Kerry’s journey towards independence and her ongoing work championing accessibility, inclusion, and equality.\n\nLiving with a disability comes with countless unseen challenges — including the heavy financial burden of medical care, mobility equipment, and everyday essentials. It often feels like the world charges you more for something you never asked for. By taking part in this golf day, you’re helping ease that burden for someone who continues to give back, inspire others, and champion change.\n\n💚 Where the funds go:\nAll proceeds will support Kerry’s essential medical and mobility needs, including:\n• Specialised medical tests\n• An upcoming operation\n• New wheelchair batteries\n• A portable basin for comfort, dignity, and independence\n\n⛳ How you can get involved:\n\nPlay in a 4-ball – R4 000\nIncludes green fees, halfway lunch, and dinner at prize giving\nSponsor a hole – R2 500\nPerfect for businesses wanting great visibility while supporting a meaningful cause\nDonate prizes\nVouchers, hampers, merchandise, or experiences are all welcome\nNot golfing? Join us for dinner – R250\n\nPlease note: Golf carts and caddies are for the player’s own account and must be booked directly with Wanderers Golf Club.\n\n📅 Date: 12 June 2026\n📍 Venue: Wanderers Golf Club\n\nTo book, sponsor, donate, or ask questions, please email Kerry at:\nkmotivationsa@gmail.com\n\nLet’s come together to support independence, dignity, and inclusion. One swing at a time, you can help champion change.\n\n#SwingForIndependence #CharityGolfDay #ChampioningChange #KmotivationSA #DisabilityAwareness #InclusionMatters\n",
