    "description": "Join us for a day of FUNdraising to support two amazing organizations, with 100% of the net proceeds going directly to Chat N Chew and the Miracle League of Keller.\n\nWe are excited to announce the beneficiaries of the 2026 Keller Services Charities Golf Classic: Chat N Chew and Miracle League of Keller. 100% of the net proceeds will go directly to these organizations. \n \nChat N Chew is a volunteer-driven nonprofit inspired by lived experiences of supporting single parents, helping them rebuild their lives with dignity and resilience. Through life coaching, transitional housing, food assistance, and community resources, we aim to ensure families not only survive but thrive. Their vision is a community where single parents and their children have the support, resources, and opportunities they need to live healthy, stable, and empowered lives.\n\nMiracle League of Keller provides children and young adults with the opportunity to play baseball regardless of ability. The Miracle League removes barriers that prevent children with mental and physical disabilities from playing on the baseball field and allows them to experience the joy of America's favorite pastime. Miracle League is about making new friends, building self-esteem, and being treated like other athletes.\n\nBoth organizations have a significant impact on our community; they rely entirely on donations from caring individuals, businesses, foundations, and events. \n\nWe aim to raise $50,000 to support these wonderful organizations. Keller Services Charities invites you to partner with us, making this an event that individuals, community members, and business professionals will want to attend. With your support, we—together—can make a meaningful difference in our local community.\n\nYour sponsorship or entry fee includes: lunch, a round of golf, a golfer goody bag, participation in the longest drive and closest-to-the-pin contests, as well as dinner and awards at the 19th hole celebration.\n\nFor more information on how you can help support this event, please get in touch with Brandy Schimmel at brandy@keller-services.com. ",
